@startuml sequence_compatibility
!theme plain
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #333
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #555
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #AAA
autonumber

title Sequence 1 — Compatibility Validation

actor "User" as U
participant "Frontend\n(Configurator)" as FE
participant "POST /api/compatibility/validate" as API
participant "CompatibilityEngine" as CE

U -> FE : Select a component\n(e.g. CPU: Ryzen 7 7700X)
FE -> API : POST /api/compatibility/validate\nbody: { cpu: {...}, motherboard: {...}, ... }
API -> CE : validateCompatibility(build)

loop for each of 6 declarative rules
  CE -> CE : rule.validate(build)\n→ null (pass) or message (fail)
end

CE -> CE : Sum TDP of all components\n(excl. PSU)\nrecommended_psu = ceil(tdp × 1.5)

CE -> CE : Check psu.wattage < recommended_psu\n→ psu_underpowered warning if true

CE --> API : { compatible, errors[], warnings[],\ntotal_tdp, recommended_psu_wattage }
API --> FE : 200 OK — CompatibilityResult

alt errors is empty
  FE --> U : Green status — build is compatible
else errors not empty
  FE --> U : Red highlight on conflicting slots\n+ French error labels from RULE_LABELS
end

note right of FE
  Rules that can fire:
  • socket_mismatch (error)
  • ram_type_mismatch (error)
  • gpu_too_long (error)
  • form_factor_mismatch (error)
  • cooler_too_tall (error)
  • ram_frequency_exceeded (warning)
  • psu_underpowered (warning)
end note

@enduml
